<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Intro</div>

<div class=itemtext>Mega Man 4 is most memorable fo its introduction of the Mega Buster and Dr. Cossack.  This is the first MM game I ever played on my own (I had previously taken a few turns playing parts of MM3).  It has 3 great weapons, the Dive Missile, Pharaoh Shot, and Drill Bomb, but surprisingly, it's not really longer than MM3.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Story</div>

<div class=itemtext>A mysteriouus cientist named Dr. Cossack, jealous of Dr. Light's fame, has challenged Mega Man to fight 8 of his own robots.  SPOILERS: This plot twist actually really surpriised me, unlike the plot twists of some other MM games.  After you defeat Dr. Cossack, Protoman appears with Dr. Cossack's daughter, Kalinka.  It seems that Wily captured Kalinka in order to make Dr. Cossack fight Mega Man.  The reason for Protoman's actions is not explained.  He was obviously working for Wily earlier, since Wily said that Protoman betrayed him.  Anyway, Mega Man eventually fights Wily, who uses what was then an INCREDIBLY cool, challenging, and unique attack, until it was copied in basically every original series sequel from that point on - disappearing and reappearing on screen to fire some energy spheres.  When Mega Man wins, Wily goes into an exit door and starts a self-destruct.  Mega Man teleports away and lands on a train that stops near Dr. Light's house.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Unique Features</div>

<div class=itemtext>This game introduced the level style of 8 master robots - 4 castle levels - 4 levels in another castle.  This style was also used in MM5 and MM6.  The Mega /buster charged shot in this game is green, a lot like the medium shot in MMX.<br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

