<td VALIGN=TOP bgcolor=ffffff class=itemtable>
<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Vulnerability Loop</div>

<div class=itemtext>Toad -> Pharaoh -> Bright -> Ring -> Drill -> Dust -> Dive -> Skull -> Toad<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Beginner's Level Orders</div>

<div class=itemtext>This boss order will make fighting Robot Masters easy, but 2 of the best wwapons are at the bottom of the list.
<p>Toad -> Bright -> Pharaoh -> Ring -> Dust -> Skull -> Dive -> Drill
<p>Dust Man is almost as easy as Toad Man, and this level order will get you the Dive Missile early, although the Pharaoh Shot is now near the bottom.
<p>Dust -> Skull -> Dive -> Drill -> Toad -> Bright -> Pharaoh -> Ring
<p>IMHO, this is the best level order if you plan to use special weapons on the Robot Masters.  Dive Man is not particularly difficult, and he's arguably easier to beat with the Mega Buster than the cumbersome Skull Barrier anyway.
<p>Dive -> Drill -> Toad -> Bright -> Pharaoh -> Ring -> Dust -> Skull<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Advanced Level Order</div>

<div class=itemtext>If you're planning to use the Mega Buster against most or all of the bosses, this level order will keep you equipped with the best weapons possible for each level.
<p>Dive -> Pharaoh -> Drill -> Toad -> Bright -> Skull -> Ring -> Dust<br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

