<td VALIGN=TOP bgcolor=ffffff class=itemtable>
<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Weapons</div>

<div class=itemtext>Dive Missile<br>
Usefulness: 10<br>
Energy Cost: 1<br>
The Dive Missile is a homing shot, and, if you use it on the right enemies, it's quite powerful, too!  It's great for basically anything that flies, especially enemies that try to attack from above or below.  Use it on the pesky helicopter enemies that launch their propellers at you (it will home in on the propellers, too), and as an unlimited-item technique with the rocks at the end of Drill Man's stage.<br>
Pharaoh Shot<br>
Usefulness: 9<br>
Energy Cost: 1,6<br>
The Pharaoh Shot fires a fireball in any of 6 directions (you can't aim it straight up or straight down).  Its normal shot has average power (usually 2-3 plasma shots), but you can charge it up as well, to make it a huge, very powerful shot (usually 6 plasma shots).  The shot will charge up and increase in size over Mega Man's head, and you can use this as a sort of "headbutt" attack, because it will hit enemies until you throw it, or it hits something that it won't defeat in one hit.  Even better, this "headbutt" attack uses no weapon energy!<br>
Drill Bomb<br>
Usefulness: 8<br>
Energy Cost: 1<br>
The impressive Drill Bomb is a drill on a rocket that explodes when it hits something.  You can also start the explosion before it hits by pressing the fire button again while it's in midair.  This is a very powerful weapon, and it will do about as much damage as 6 plasma shots against most large enemies.<br>
Flash Stopper<br>
Usefulness: 7<br>
Energy Cost: 4<br>
The Flash Stopper is an improved version of Flash Man's Time Stopper from Mega Man 2.  With this flash, you can use your arm cannon while enemies are stopped.  And unllike the Time Stopper, the Flash Stopper doesn't use all of its energy in one shot.  These 2 improvements make it a very formidable tool.<br>
Rain Flush<br>
Usefulness: 6<br>
Energy Cost: 4<br>
The Rain Flush was the first full-screen offensive attack in the Mega Man series.  Mega Man launches a pod into the sky, and rain starts falling several seconds afterward.  It's quite powerful, and the attack lasts for several secods, so it's possible to hit powerful enemies more than once with each shot.  However, the delay between firing and the attack and the high weapon energy cost make it a weapon for special situations - mostly when several tough enemies are on the screen at once, or against mini-bosses.  This is a great weapon against the wall cannons in Ring Man's stage, and in situations in which you have to run past a lot of enemies that are difficult to fire at, like on the swinging platforms at the end of Bright Man's stage.<br>
Skull Barrier<br>
Usefulness: 3<br>
Energy Cost: 2<br>
The Skull Barrier protects Mega Man with a rotating shield.  Unlike the Leaf Shield, it will block or attack just one enemy or shot, but you can walk with it.  It's useful when you have to jump over holes that have enemies jumping out of them, but it isn't very powerful or energy-efficient.<br>
Ring Boomerang<br>
Usefulness: 3<br>
Energy Cost: 1/2<br>
The Ring Boomerang fires forward and quickly returns.  It's not very powerful, but it will go through shields.<br>
Dust Crusher<br>
Usefulness: 2<br>
Energy Cost: 1<br>
The Dust Crusher fires a cube of compact dust and junk.  The shot will split into 4 shots that will fire in 4 diagonal directions when it hits.  It would be a lot more useful if you could fire the diagonal shots before it hit, like what you can do with the Drill Bomb.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Items</div>

<div class=itemtext>Rush Coil<br>
Energy Cost: 2<br>
Rush will stand it front of Mega Man, and Mega Man can use him as a springboard.  The MM4 version is more energy-efficient than the MM3 version.  You get the Rush Coil at the beginning of the game.<br>
Rush Jet<br>
Energy Cost: Varies<br>
The Rush Jet is actually slightly different in every MM game.  MM4's Rush Jet flies forward, although you can press up or down to move it diagonally.  You get the Rush Jet after Drill Man's stage.<br>
Rush Marine<br>
Energy Cost: Varies<br>
This is really a lot like an underwater version of the MM3 Rush Jet, although plasma shots are fired from Rush's mouth instead of Mega Man's arm cannon.  You get the Rush Marine after Toad Man's stage, and it's most useful in Dive Man's stage.<br>
Wire, Balloon, E-Tank<br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

